                            "text": "Given two singly linked lists, determine if the two lists intersect. Return the intersecting node. Intersection is defined based on reference, not value. Two-pointer trick: each pointer traverses both lists; if an intersection exists, the pointers align after at most two passes. If not, both reach null."
